Strategy for the automated players - for the Naive and Whatever player,
    exactly as detailed in the PDF.
    Naive is iterating though the rows and columns, and the Whatever is just guessing.
    The Smart player tries to block the naive first and uses his position
    to fill in a row. If that failed, he will resort to Naive strategy.

The advantage of an interface for players in program design is standardizing the
    "what" of players, without detailing the "how". Using these principle, it
    is straightforward to add different players at any time, and makes the ability
    to work with other devs easier. This is the basis of Abstraction and Encapsulation.

I added a private enum, the enum means which wintype has occured - X, O or non yet